name: integer_i16_zero
description: |
  Zero is the i16 additive identity and the critical invalid divisor for integer
  division and remainder. Pairing it with one exercises divide-by-zero handling,
  which may trap, raise an exception, return an error, or be undefined depending
  on the language and execution environment.
format: hex
decode-as: i16
pair:
  - with: one.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i16"
  - "zero"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "remainder-by-zero"
  - "baseline"
---
00 00 # 0
